Following is a summary of  Sao Paulo ’s 
FIPE weekly consumer prices report from the Foundation Economics 
Research Institute in Sao Paulo.  NOTE: * This data covers a period of 8 weeks of data collection, based on   families with a total incomes ranging from a multiple of 1 times to 20   times the national  minimum wage . The final figures represent the most      recent 4 weeks of inflation. This is calculated using the prior  4 weeks as a base period.  SOURCE: Fundação Instituto de Pesquisas Econômicas (FIPE)  To contact the reporter on this story:
